div.p:
THE Best part of the Fortune of my last Play

 (The Innocent Adultery

) was, that it gave me an Opportunity of making my self known to Your Grace. You were pleased to countenance the Advances which I had been a great while directing and aiming at You, and have since encourag'd me into an Industry, which, I hope, will allow me in this Play to own (which is the only way I can) the great Obligations I have to You.

